      skos:note "'LLMs become not just a tool for conversation or coding, but a compiler that takes a narrative architecture and produces a synthetic individual whose every thought projects far further down the paths we set than we could tread alone.' Identified as the cleanest one-sentence statement of the mechanism yet written — extends the committed narrative-as-program and code-as-compilation threads and should survive every edit." .

